This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for analyzing aerial videos, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of drones and spatiotemporal graphs also suggests that it may be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Markov Chain Monte Carlo and dynamic programming, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
